WEBVTT

00:01.710 --> 00:03.169
{\an5}WOW!

00:01.710 --> 00:03.169
Girl: ♪ I GOT THE BEAT ♪

00:03.253 --> 00:05.338
♪ SO ALL THE KIDS DANCE
WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:05.422 --> 00:08.550
♪ PICK IT UP, TURN AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:08.633 --> 00:11.428
[♪...]

00:12.846 --> 00:14.305
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, HEY) ♪

00:14.389 --> 00:16.599
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, WOW) ♪

00:16.683 --> 00:17.892
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:17.976 --> 00:21.479
♪ I GOT THE BEAT SO ALL THE KIDS
DANCE WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:21.563 --> 00:25.525
♪ STICK 'EM UP ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:25.608 --> 00:29.195
[♪...]

00:29.279 --> 00:31.322
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:31.406 --> 00:33.324
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B. ♪

00:33.408 --> 00:35.702
{\an8}Captioning Provided By:
MTV NETWORKS

00:36.035 --> 00:40.039
[♪...]

00:47.046 --> 00:49.466
Man: SAGGING... SAGGING...

00:49.549 --> 00:52.010
I'M SAGGING ALL OVER THE PLACE.

00:52.093 --> 00:54.721
I MUST'VE MISSED A KNOT.

00:54.804 --> 00:58.641
HOW CAN I HANG MY BEGONIAS
WITH A SAGGY PLANT HOLDER?

00:58.725 --> 01:01.102
{\an3}THAT'S WHY WE
MEET IN THE CIRCLE, ANTON

01:01.186 --> 01:02.562
{\an3}TO NURTURE EACH OTHER
THROUGH OUR MACRAMÉ EMERGENCIES.

01:02.645 --> 01:05.815
OH, PLEASE.

01:05.899 --> 01:07.317
LA, LA-LA, LA-LA- OH.

01:07.400 --> 01:09.652
WE HAVE VISITORS,
WHAT A SURPRISE.

01:09.736 --> 01:11.821
AND A COINCIDENCE.

01:11.905 --> 01:14.616
WHAT WITH ME AND ALL THIS
TAFFY TO SELL.

01:14.699 --> 01:15.742
[BELL DINGS]

01:15.825 --> 01:19.496
{\an1}BESSIE, YOU KNOW IT'S NOT POLITE
TO HUSTLE OUR GUESTS.

01:19.579 --> 01:21.039
{\an1}LADIES, I'M TRYING TO
CONCENTRATE.

01:21.122 --> 01:24.542
{\an3}OOH, WHAT YOU GOT THERE,
MR. SAINT GERMAN?

01:24.626 --> 01:26.753
{\an3}HEY, ARE YOU TRYING TO
TIE A MAVERICK KNOT?

01:26.836 --> 01:31.508
{\an6}YOU'LL NEVER GET IT TO TIGHTEN
UNLESS YOU FLIP THE DOLPHIN
AFTER YOU SWAB THE DECK.

01:31.591 --> 01:33.343
{\an1}[GRUNTS]

01:33.426 --> 01:36.012
{\an3}OH, I GOT THE KNOT-A-LOT BADGE
LIKE THREE, FOUR YEARS AGO.

01:36.095 --> 01:37.931
{\an3}SO, YOU KNOW, KNOTS ARE
KIND OF MY JAM.

01:38.014 --> 01:41.017
{\an1}THEN YOU FINISH IT
IF YOU'RE SO CRAFTY.

01:41.100 --> 01:42.227
{\an3}YOU GOT IT.

01:42.310 --> 01:43.853
{\an3}IT'S A LITTLE KNOWN FACT
THAT THE MAVERICK KNOT

01:43.937 --> 01:45.063
{\an3}WAS INVENTED DURING
THE GOLDEN AGE OF PIRATES

01:45.146 --> 01:47.524
ON THE SAILING VESSEL KNOWN
AS THE QUEEN ANNE'S REVENGE

01:47.607 --> 01:48.983
{\an3}[SPEAKING QUICKER] BY OBSCURE
FIRST MATE SPANKY ROGERS.

01:49.067 --> 01:50.235
{\an6}HE NEEDED A STRONG KNOT TO TIE
FIRECRACKERS INTO
BLACKBEARD'S BEARD

01:50.318 --> 01:52.862
{\an3}BEFORE HE WENT INTO BATTLES
ON THE OPEN SEA. [GASPS]

01:52.946 --> 01:54.197
HERE YOU GO.

01:54.280 --> 01:57.992
I HACKED THE PATTERN AND
PUSHED IT ABOUT 48 KNOTS.

01:58.076 --> 02:02.247
DON'T YOU... LIKE IT?

02:04.666 --> 02:06.960
IT'S...

02:07.043 --> 02:10.880
IT'S THE MOST BEAUTIFUL THING
I'VE EVER SEEN.

02:10.964 --> 02:11.923
COULD YOU HELP ME WITH MY VEST?

02:12.006 --> 02:14.217
DOES THIS LOOK UNEVEN TO YOU?

02:14.300 --> 02:16.386
[GROANS]

02:16.469 --> 02:18.513
MAKE IT FAR OUT, MAN.

02:18.596 --> 02:22.517
WOW, THIS IS A GATEWAY INTO
A WHOLE NEW WORLD.

02:24.102 --> 02:26.312
Mom: SWEETIE, TIME FOR BED.

02:26.396 --> 02:27.730
Bessie: JUST A COUPLE
MORE KNOTS.

02:27.814 --> 02:31.484
Mom: GO TO BED, BESSIE.

02:31.568 --> 02:34.654
OK, OK, I'M WRAPPING IT UP.

02:34.737 --> 02:35.697
[OWL HOOTING]

02:35.780 --> 02:38.366
Mom: BESSIE, BED.

02:38.449 --> 02:40.660
TURNING OUT THE LIGHT RIGHT NOW.

02:40.743 --> 02:42.203
OH, CAN'T STOP.

02:52.922 --> 02:58.261
IT'S A GLORIOUS DAY TO MACRAMÉ.

02:58.344 --> 03:00.597
[SCREAMS]

03:00.680 --> 03:01.598
WHOO.

03:01.681 --> 03:05.476
I AM SORRY, SIR.

03:05.560 --> 03:08.563
BUT NO SHOES, NO SERVICE.

03:08.646 --> 03:10.064
[FLIES BUZZING]

03:10.148 --> 03:15.194
{\an6}SHOES ARE JUST THE MAN'S WAY
OF KEEPING US DISCONNECTED
FROM THE EARTH.

03:15.278 --> 03:16.279
I'VE GOT AN EASY SOLUTION.

03:20.366 --> 03:21.576
TABLE FOR ONE, PLEASE.

03:21.659 --> 03:25.121
[GROANS] THIS WAY.

03:25.204 --> 03:28.791
{\an3}I'LL HAVE A CUP OF HOT WATER
AND SOME KETCHUP.

03:28.875 --> 03:30.251
[CARS CRASHING]

03:34.631 --> 03:37.342
[♪...]

03:41.888 --> 03:42.722
THANKS, HON.

03:42.805 --> 03:44.807
[LAUGHS] NO NEED.

03:44.891 --> 03:46.976
I AM MERELY A VESSEL
FOR THE MACRAMÉ.

03:47.060 --> 03:48.645
[COINS JINGLING]

03:55.526 --> 03:56.986
CHANGE PROTECTORS?

03:57.070 --> 03:59.864
WHO COULD ASK FOR ANYTHING MORE?

04:04.035 --> 04:05.995
EXCELLENT WORK TODAY, FINGER.

04:06.079 --> 04:08.456
GIVE YOURSELF A NICE STRETCH.

04:11.918 --> 04:13.044
OW.

04:13.127 --> 04:13.419
FINGER.

04:19.216 --> 04:21.010
I'VE BEEN THINKING TOO SMALL.

04:21.094 --> 04:24.055
THAT POINTY BUILDING WAS JUST
AN ACCIDENT WAITING TO HAPPEN.

04:24.138 --> 04:26.933
BUT THANKS TO
THE POWER OF MACRAMÉ

04:27.016 --> 04:30.853
NO CITIZEN OF SAN FRANCISCO EVER
NEED LIVE SO DANGEROUSLY AGAIN.

04:30.937 --> 04:32.647
SUCK IT UP, FINGER, LET'S GO.

04:32.730 --> 04:38.111
[♪...]

04:39.654 --> 04:42.281
[SEALS BARKING...]

04:52.083 --> 04:55.086
[BARKING]

04:55.169 --> 04:59.424
[♪...]

05:04.512 --> 05:06.723
IT'S... BEAUTIFUL.

05:06.806 --> 05:09.517
{\an3}IT'S, IT'S THE MOST
AMAZING THING I'VE EVER SEEN.

05:09.600 --> 05:11.310
{\an3}I LOVE IT.

05:11.394 --> 05:15.481
WHEE...

05:15.565 --> 05:19.610
[LAUGHTER]

05:22.655 --> 05:24.032
[SNORING]

05:24.115 --> 05:26.409
[BELLS JINGLING]

05:26.492 --> 05:28.661
BESSIE, COME IN, BESSIE.

05:28.745 --> 05:29.370
IT'S SANTA CLAUS.

05:29.454 --> 05:32.457
CHRISTMAS NEEDS YOU, BESSIE.

05:32.540 --> 05:34.042
YES, SANTA, I'M HERE.

05:34.125 --> 05:35.585
HO, HO, HO, BESSIE.

05:35.668 --> 05:37.211
THANK GOODNESS.

05:37.295 --> 05:38.588
WHAT DO YOU NEED, SANTA?

05:38.671 --> 05:40.965
{\an3}MY SUPER SPEED, MY LASER
HEARING, MY PEOPLE SKILLS?

05:41.049 --> 05:44.927
NO, TONIGHT I NEED...

05:45.011 --> 05:46.429
MACRAMÉ.

05:46.512 --> 05:47.805
TALK TO ME.

05:47.889 --> 05:50.933
WE'VE HAD AN UNUSUALLY
LARGE ORDERS OF PLANT HOLDERS

05:51.017 --> 05:53.478
AND THE ELVES
JUST CAN'T KEEP UP.

05:53.561 --> 05:56.606
DON'T WORRY, SANTA, I'M ON IT.

05:56.689 --> 05:58.107
Santa: WHAT A RELIEF.

05:58.191 --> 06:02.070
HOW WOULD YOU LIKE TO RIDE IN
THE SLEIGH THIS CHRISTMAS?

06:02.153 --> 06:03.821
[BUZZING]

06:03.905 --> 06:07.241
["JINGLE BELLS" PLAYING]

06:11.454 --> 06:13.581
OH, SANTA, HUH.

06:13.664 --> 06:15.792
{\an5}[SNORES] EVEN SANTA
NEEDS A BEST FRIEND,
WELL, I'LL BE THAT.

06:15.875 --> 06:17.960
[SNORES]

06:18.044 --> 06:19.921
[WIND BLOWING...]

06:20.797 --> 06:24.467
[BUOY BELL RINGS]

06:24.550 --> 06:25.051
[FOG HORN BLOWS]

06:25.134 --> 06:26.844
[BIRDS SQUAWKING]

06:41.317 --> 06:43.402
HOO, WHAT'S THAT HORRIBLE STINK?

06:50.576 --> 06:51.994
[GAGS]

06:52.078 --> 06:54.622
WET WOOL, UGH.

06:54.705 --> 06:55.790
[BABY CRYING]

06:55.873 --> 07:02.171
THIS HORRIBLE SMELL
IS RUINING EVERYONE'S APPETITE.

07:02.839 --> 07:04.006
EW...

07:04.090 --> 07:08.678
MY CHANGE IS ITCHY,
MOIST AND STINKY.

07:08.761 --> 07:11.848
THIS HAS GOTTEN WAY OUT OF HAND.

07:11.931 --> 07:14.475
I HAD TO CANCEL THE CRAFT FAIR.

07:14.559 --> 07:17.478
{\an1}YEAH, EVERY MACRAMÉ JOINT
IN TOWN IS SHUT DOWN.

07:17.562 --> 07:18.688
NO MORE WOOL.

07:18.771 --> 07:19.689
FORGET WOOL.

07:19.772 --> 07:22.275
I CAN'T FIND ANY
ANGORA CASHMERE YARN ANYWHERE.

07:22.358 --> 07:24.652
ANTON DOES NOT
KNOT WITH SYNTHETICS.

07:26.612 --> 07:30.950
OH, IS THERE ANYTHING
THAT ISN'T BETTER WITH MACRAMÉ?

07:31.033 --> 07:35.121
FLY, BE FREE.

07:37.665 --> 07:40.209
HEY, SWEETIE, DO YOU HAVE A SEC?

07:40.293 --> 07:42.545
NOT NOW MOM, THERE'S
A WHOLE WORLD TO MACRAMÉ.

07:42.628 --> 07:44.714
WELL, THAT'S JUST IT.

07:44.797 --> 07:46.465
YOUR MACRAMÉ
IS EXTREMELY CREATIVE

07:46.549 --> 07:49.510
AND I'M SURE
EVERYONE APPRECIATES...

07:49.594 --> 07:50.803
SAY NO MORE.

07:50.887 --> 07:53.097
{\an1}SEEING THE PEOPLE I LOVE
WARM AND SAFE

07:53.181 --> 07:55.725
IS ALL THE THANKS I NEED.

07:55.808 --> 07:57.894
{\an1}I EVEN SAVED
THE SKYDIVING CLUB MONEY

07:57.977 --> 07:59.896
BY MAKING THEM ALL
MACRAMÉ PARACHUTES.

07:59.979 --> 08:00.897
HI, YOU GUYS.

08:00.980 --> 08:04.233
[SCREAMING]

08:04.317 --> 08:06.068
[GRUNTING]

08:06.152 --> 08:07.862
I'M OK...

08:07.945 --> 08:09.030
[SIGHS]

08:09.113 --> 08:10.364
B., LISTEN TO ME.

08:10.448 --> 08:11.073
YOU GOTTA STOP <i> NOW.</i>

08:11.157 --> 08:12.783
PLEASE, STOP.

08:12.867 --> 08:14.702
STOP?

08:14.785 --> 08:17.747
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU PEOPLE?

08:17.830 --> 08:20.041
ISN'T THE MACRAMÉ CIRCLE'S MOTTO

08:20.124 --> 08:21.500
"GIVE ME MACRAMÉ
OR GIVE ME DEATH"?

08:24.629 --> 08:27.840
MAYBE YOUR HANDS ARE ACHING
AND YOUR SPIRITS ARE FLAGGING

08:27.924 --> 08:29.800
BUT NOT MINE.

08:29.884 --> 08:32.094
I WON'T GIVE UP UNTIL
THIS GREAT, BIG WORLD

08:32.178 --> 08:33.596
IS SNUG AS A BUG IN A RUG.

08:33.679 --> 08:38.433
UH, GOLLY, GEE, BESSIE, WHEN YOU
PUT IT THAT WAY, I, UH...

08:38.517 --> 08:41.270
{\an3}AH-HA, LET'S SEE YOU
KNOT NOW, MISSY.

08:42.688 --> 08:45.399
[GASPS]

08:45.483 --> 08:47.109
BUT... PLEASE... LET'S...

08:47.193 --> 08:49.779
LET ME JUST... [GRUNTS]

08:49.862 --> 08:50.571
I HAVE A...

08:50.655 --> 08:53.282
[GASPS] YOUR MACRAMÉ IS STRONG.

08:53.366 --> 08:56.077
BUT GUESS WHAT,
MINE IS STRONGER.

08:59.538 --> 09:02.750
{\an3}[SCREAMS]

09:02.833 --> 09:04.961
OH, NO NEED TO RUMBLE.

09:05.044 --> 09:07.964
BESSIE, MY FRIEND,
YOUR GIFT IS GREAT.

09:08.047 --> 09:09.131
BUT IT IS NOT WITHOUT
A HIGH COST.

09:09.215 --> 09:11.092
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

09:11.175 --> 09:12.134
FOLLOW ME.

09:12.218 --> 09:15.972
SEE THAT, BESSIE?

09:16.055 --> 09:17.473
[GASPS] NAKED SHEEP?

09:17.557 --> 09:19.976
THE POOR LITTLE GUYS,
THEY LOOK SO COLD.

09:20.059 --> 09:22.186
{\an1}[BAAS]

09:22.270 --> 09:24.105
BUMMER, HUH?

09:24.188 --> 09:25.439
THEY NEED THEIR WOOL
IN THE WINTER MONTHS.

09:25.523 --> 09:28.526
WELL, SO WHY DID THEY
SHAVE THEM?

09:28.609 --> 09:31.320
THE YARN CONGLOMERATES
NEEDED THEIR WOOL

09:31.404 --> 09:34.240
TO MAKE ENOUGH TO SUPPLY
YOUR MASSIVE MACRAMÉ NEEDS.

09:34.323 --> 09:36.158
WHAT, WHAT HAVE I DONE?

09:36.242 --> 09:39.412
THE QUESTION, BESSIE...

09:39.495 --> 09:42.790
IS WHAT ARE YOU
<i>GOING</i> TO DO? [LAUGHS]

09:46.085 --> 09:48.963
[GRUNTING]

09:53.718 --> 09:57.888
{\an3}[LAUGHS] YEAH, BESSIE,
DO IT. [LAUGHS]

10:11.444 --> 10:12.611
[SQUAWKS]

10:15.948 --> 10:19.243
[GRUNTING...]

10:22.955 --> 10:26.709
[GASPING AND GRUNTING...]

10:35.217 --> 10:36.302
[BARKING]

10:42.850 --> 10:46.896
[BAAING]

10:46.979 --> 10:51.233
DO YOU THINK ANYONE WILL
REMEMBER THE DAY I MACRAMÉD?

10:51.317 --> 10:54.111
{\an1}WE WILL.

10:51.317 --> 10:54.111
{\an3}WE WILL.

10:55.988 --> 11:00.201
[♪...]

11:06.999 --> 11:08.250
Ben: HOT...

11:08.334 --> 11:09.251
[GROANS]

11:09.335 --> 11:12.213
HOT, HOT... HOT.

11:12.296 --> 11:15.049
HOT... PLEASE.

11:15.132 --> 11:15.674
{\an5}HUH, OH...

11:15.132 --> 11:15.674
[♪...]

11:19.303 --> 11:20.596
[GRUNTS]

11:20.679 --> 11:23.933
♪ AH... ♪

11:24.016 --> 11:25.684
[♪...]

11:25.768 --> 11:27.603
[LAUGHING]

11:27.686 --> 11:30.815
[GRUNTING]

11:30.898 --> 11:32.900
WHAT'S IT GONNA BE, SPARKY?

11:32.983 --> 11:35.277
ONE SHUTTLE POP, HAL.

11:35.361 --> 11:35.778
[CASH REGISTER DINGS]

11:35.861 --> 11:39.365
[GASPS AND GRUNTS]

11:39.448 --> 11:42.284
{\an3}SO A LEPRECHAUN WALKS INTO A BAR
AND ORDERS A MILKSHAKE.

11:42.368 --> 11:45.454
{\an6}OH, WAIT, NO, UGH,
YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO KNOW
THAT HE'S A LEPRECHAUN YET.

11:45.538 --> 11:47.706
OK, START OVER, START OVER.

11:47.790 --> 11:51.669
{\an6}SO A SMALL MAN
WALKS INTO A BAR AND...

11:47.790 --> 11:51.669
[♪...]

11:51.752 --> 11:54.338
{\an3}OH, HI, HAL,
KEEPING COOL? [LAUGHS]

11:56.215 --> 11:57.758
[GASPS]

11:57.842 --> 11:58.634
"HOW'S MY DRIVING?"

11:58.717 --> 12:01.095
OH, HAL, HEY, HAL, HAL...

12:01.178 --> 12:02.471
HAL... [COUGHS]

12:02.555 --> 12:06.267
HAL, [COUGHS],
YOUR DRIVING, [COUGHS]

12:06.350 --> 12:08.144
I WANT TO TELL YOU
ABOUT IT, HAL.

12:08.227 --> 12:10.646
HUH. [COUGHS]

12:10.729 --> 12:13.816
I GUESS HE DIDN'T,
[COUGHS], HEAR ME.

12:13.899 --> 12:15.317
FIVE-FIVE-FIVE...

12:15.401 --> 12:19.822
[PHONE RINGING]

12:19.905 --> 12:21.157
ICE CREAM.

12:21.240 --> 12:23.742
Bessie: Oh, hi, Hal,
it's Bessie... Higgenbottom.

12:23.826 --> 12:26.704
Boy, you peeled off
in a big hurry this afternoon.

12:26.787 --> 12:29.123
I DID, DID I?

12:29.206 --> 12:30.583
YOU SURE DID, HAL.

12:30.666 --> 12:33.377
BUT LUCKY FOR YOU, I HAVE
A SEMI-PHOTOGRAPHIC MEMORY

12:33.461 --> 12:35.004
AND I CAUGHT THE NUMBER
ON YOUR BUMPER STICKER.

12:35.087 --> 12:36.839
THE ONE ABOUT YOUR DRIVING.

12:36.922 --> 12:38.841
SO ANYWAY, SINCE YOU ASKED...

12:38.924 --> 12:41.051
{\an5}I THOUGHT YOU SHOULD KNOW THAT
YOU BLEW RIGHT THROUGH
THAT STOP SIGN.

12:41.135 --> 12:43.304
[COUGHS]

12:43.387 --> 12:45.014
BLEW THROUGH A STOP SIGN?!

12:45.097 --> 12:46.015
WHERE?!

12:46.098 --> 12:47.558
WHEN?!

12:47.641 --> 12:50.352
Bessie: At the corner of
Ginsberg and Divisadero.

12:50.436 --> 12:54.190
At, let's see, 2:37 p.m.,
Pacific Standard Time.

12:54.273 --> 12:57.151
HAL, YOU COULD'VE HIT
A CHICKEN CROSSING THE ROAD.

12:57.234 --> 12:59.028
I GOT YOU, I GOT YOU,
THANKS, GIRLIE.

12:59.111 --> 13:00.696
YEAH, YOU KNOW,
THAT'S WHAT FRIENDS ARE...

13:00.779 --> 13:02.072
[DIAL TONE HUMS]

13:02.156 --> 13:03.449
HMM.

13:03.532 --> 13:06.911
HAL SOUNDS HUSKIER ON THE PHONE.

13:09.288 --> 13:13.375
Boss: HAL...

13:13.459 --> 13:14.126
GET IN HERE!

13:14.210 --> 13:15.628
{\an3}OF ALL THE NUMBSKULL
THINGS TO DO

13:15.711 --> 13:18.297
{\an3}YOU ROLL RIGHT THROUGH
A STOP SIGN?

13:18.380 --> 13:21.383
{\an3}THAT'S WHY IT SAYS
"STOP," PINHEAD.

13:21.467 --> 13:22.801
'CAUSE YOU'RE SUPPOSED TO STOP.

13:22.885 --> 13:26.013
{\an3}THAT KID REPORTS US,
YOU KNOW THE FINE I GOTTA PAY?

13:26.096 --> 13:26.555
BUT BOSS, I...

13:26.639 --> 13:28.974
SAVE IT, SAVE IT.

13:29.058 --> 13:32.394
{\an4}ONE MORE STUNT LIKE THAT
AND YOU'LL NEVER SELL ANOTHER
SHUTTLE POP

13:32.478 --> 13:33.479
{\an1}OR FUDGE ROCKET
IN THIS TOWN AGAIN.

13:33.562 --> 13:36.315
YOU UNDERSTAND, YOU'RE FINISHED!

13:36.398 --> 13:39.068
[SIZZLING]

13:39.151 --> 13:40.736
[GROANING]

13:40.819 --> 13:41.362
{\an5}[GASPING]

13:40.819 --> 13:41.362
[♪...]

13:41.445 --> 13:45.032
[CLAMORING]

13:51.121 --> 13:52.373
[SIGHS]

13:52.456 --> 13:55.751
THE USUAL, PLEASE.

13:55.834 --> 13:58.254
UM, CAN I PLEASE HAVE
SOME SYRUP ON IT?

13:58.337 --> 14:00.756
NO.

14:00.839 --> 14:02.800
{\an3}WELL, THAT DOESN'T
SEEM VERY FAIR.

14:02.883 --> 14:05.427
LIFE ISN'T FAIR,
YOU'RE WELCOME.

14:05.511 --> 14:06.679
{\an3}THANK YOU.

14:06.762 --> 14:08.222
{\an3}[GASPING]

14:08.305 --> 14:10.683
{\an3}HEY, HAL, GREAT CHATTING
WITH YOU YESTERDAY.

14:10.766 --> 14:12.893
{\an3}WE SHOULD DO THAT
MORE OFTEN, REMEMBER?

14:12.977 --> 14:14.937
{\an3}REMEMBER ON THE TELEPHONE,
STOP SIGN?

14:15.020 --> 14:18.649
{\an3}WHAT, ARE YOU HAVING
A BRAIN FREEZE? [LAUGHS]

14:18.732 --> 14:20.276
Hal: IT WAS YOU.

14:20.359 --> 14:23.779
AH, SO, UM...

14:23.862 --> 14:24.446
A SHUTTLE POP
FOR MY GENTLEMAN FRIEND

14:24.530 --> 14:28.033
AND FOR ME...

14:28.117 --> 14:32.871
HMM...

14:34.873 --> 14:37.376
{\an3}OH, WHO AM I KIDDING,
A FUDGE ROCKET.

14:37.459 --> 14:38.502
OH, TOO BAD.

14:38.586 --> 14:40.337
WE'RE OUT OF FUDGE ROCKETS.

14:40.421 --> 14:43.424
AND SHUTTLE POPS.

14:43.507 --> 14:46.343
{\an3}OH, HIGHLY UNUSUAL,
BUT NONETHELESS POSSIBLE.

14:46.427 --> 14:48.470
IN THAT CASE, WE'LL HAVE...

14:48.554 --> 14:50.222
ICE CREAM SANDWICH,
ICE CREAM SANDWICH.

14:50.306 --> 14:53.434
OH, JUST SOLD MY LAST ONE.

14:53.517 --> 14:55.978
{\an3}[WHIMPERS]

14:56.061 --> 14:57.313
COME DOWN, BEN, HANDLING THIS.

14:57.396 --> 14:58.606
OK, TWO CRUNCH CONES.

14:58.689 --> 15:00.149
DISCONTINUED.

15:00.232 --> 15:02.818
OH, WELL, UM, MAYBE YOU SHOULD
TAKE DOWN THE PICTURE.

15:02.901 --> 15:04.653
OH, I FEEL SICK.

15:04.737 --> 15:07.823
OK, MOVING INTO FIRST POSITION,
GRAPE-SICLES.

15:07.906 --> 15:09.033
NOPE.

15:09.116 --> 15:10.159
OH, BOY, OVERHEATING.

15:10.242 --> 15:11.827
NEED SOMETHING COLD
AND DELICIOUS.

15:11.910 --> 15:15.873
{\an1}BEN, BEN, BEN, BEN, BEN,
DON'T MAKE A SCENE.

15:15.956 --> 15:16.665
NOTHING TO SEE HERE, FOLKS.

15:16.749 --> 15:19.001
{\an5}[ENGINE RUMBLES]

15:16.749 --> 15:19.001
[♪...]

15:19.084 --> 15:21.629
{\an3}HEY, WAIT,
YOU CAN'T DO THIS TO HIM.

15:21.712 --> 15:23.422
WE'LL TAKE ANYTHING.

15:23.505 --> 15:26.091
ORANGE POPS, CONE CRUMBS.

15:26.175 --> 15:27.468
A HANDFUL OF PEANUTS.

15:27.551 --> 15:29.094
ANYTHING!

15:30.679 --> 15:36.226
NO...

15:36.310 --> 15:40.272
[♪...]

15:40.356 --> 15:45.778
[CHILDREN CLAMORING...]

15:47.363 --> 15:48.864
OH, BOY.

15:48.947 --> 15:52.242
HAVE I GOT SOMETHING SPECIAL
FOR YOU TWO.

15:52.326 --> 15:56.538
[GASPING] HEY.

15:56.622 --> 15:58.916
[GASPING AND GRUNTING...]

16:00.125 --> 16:02.252
HEY, HEY...

16:02.336 --> 16:04.004
WAIT...

16:04.088 --> 16:05.798
THANK YOU, ICE CREAM MAN.

16:05.881 --> 16:07.091
NUM-NUM-NUM-NUM.

16:07.174 --> 16:08.425
OH, ICE CREAM, I LOVE YOU.

16:08.509 --> 16:10.219
Bessie: PST, PST.

16:10.302 --> 16:11.679
PENNY.

16:12.805 --> 16:13.681
{\an3}PENNY.

16:13.764 --> 16:15.891
{\an1}HI, BESSIE,
WHERE'S YOUR ICE CREAM?

16:15.974 --> 16:18.394
{\an3}UM, HARD TO EXPLAIN,
COSMIC FORCES.

16:18.477 --> 16:22.064
HEY, WOULD YOU MIND PROCURING
A COUPLE SHUTTLE POPS FOR ME?

16:22.147 --> 16:23.982
{\an1}UH, I DON'T FEEL
COMFORTABLE WITH THAT.

16:24.066 --> 16:26.902
BUT I'LL GO GET THEM FOR YOU.

16:27.778 --> 16:30.322
{\an3}ICE CREAM MAN,
TWO SHUTTLE POPS, PLEASE.

16:32.616 --> 16:36.078
{\an1}YOU'VE ALREADY HAD YOUR
ICE CREAM TODAY, LEFKOWITZ.

16:36.161 --> 16:38.288
I, UH, UH, THEY WERE DELICIOUS.

16:38.372 --> 16:40.374
{\an3}MM...

16:40.457 --> 16:41.625
WHO YOU BUYING FOR?

16:41.709 --> 16:42.584
BESSIE AND BEN.

16:42.668 --> 16:44.878
{\an1}OVER THERE, THE ONES
HIDING UNDER THE TREE.

16:44.962 --> 16:47.423
{\an1}HEY, GUYS, HEY, BESSIE,
HEY, BEN, WAVE.

16:47.506 --> 16:50.759
THOSE DOUBLE-CROSSERS?

16:50.843 --> 16:53.387
I QUIT THIS NEIGHBORHOOD

16:53.470 --> 16:55.931
EFFECTIVE IMMEDIATELY!

16:56.014 --> 16:57.766
GAME OVER.

16:57.850 --> 16:59.935
NO MORE ICE CREAM SOLD HERE.

17:00.018 --> 17:04.231
AND YOU CAN THANK
YOUR <i> SNITCH</i> FRIEND...

17:04.314 --> 17:06.108
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM.

17:06.191 --> 17:07.067
[GASPS]

17:12.196 --> 17:15.117
HAL, WHAT HAS GOTTEN INTO YOU?

17:15.200 --> 17:16.577
WE'RE YOUR BEST CUSTOMERS.

17:16.660 --> 17:19.163
{\an1}BEST CUSTOMERS DON'T
RAT YOU OUT TO THE BOSS

17:19.246 --> 17:24.667
{\an1}JUST 'CAUSE YOU HAPPEN TO SLIDE
PAST A TEENY LITTLE STOP SIGN

17:24.752 --> 17:27.796
{\an1}ONE TIME IN OVER
10 YEARS OF SERVICE!

17:27.880 --> 17:30.007
HAL, I'M SORRY.

17:30.090 --> 17:32.634
{\an3}I WAS JUST DOING WHAT YOUR
BUMPER STICKER CLEARLY ADVISED.

17:32.718 --> 17:34.470
YEAH, SURE.

17:34.553 --> 17:37.598
WELL, NOW YOU CAN SUCK ICE CUBES
FOR THE REST OF THE SUMMER.

17:37.681 --> 17:40.017
ALL OF YOU!

17:40.100 --> 17:41.477
[SCREAMS]

17:41.560 --> 17:45.022
[CRYING AND GROANING...]

17:46.398 --> 17:48.525
[CRYING]

17:48.609 --> 17:53.155
["FUNERAL MARCH" PLAYS...]

17:55.908 --> 17:59.661
Bessie: BENJAMIN,
COME ON, OPEN UP, PLEASE?

17:59.745 --> 18:01.705
YOU RUINED MY WHOLE SUMMER.

18:01.789 --> 18:05.334
I DIDN'T GET TO GO TO SPACE CAMP
OR TAKE SYNCHRONIZED SWIMMING.

18:05.417 --> 18:08.712
THE ONLY THING I HAD TO
LOOK FORWARD TO WAS ICE CREAM

18:08.796 --> 18:12.090
AND YOU RUINED IT. [CRIES]

18:16.804 --> 18:22.059
{\an3}LET ME GUESS, FROZEN LENTIL SOUP
AND FISH STICKS?

18:22.142 --> 18:22.559
WHAT?

18:22.643 --> 18:24.019
Bessie: SHH, SHH.

18:24.102 --> 18:26.438
{\an1}SOMETHING'S COMING TO ME,
DON'T SCARE IT AWAY.

18:26.522 --> 18:31.819
[♪...]

18:31.902 --> 18:33.278
[BESSIE GASPS] NUTS.

18:36.115 --> 18:39.034
{\an3}[SIGHS] ALL RIGHT, HAPPY,
LET'S MAKE A DEAL.

18:39.117 --> 18:41.787
[GRUNTING]

18:42.538 --> 18:45.499
{\an3}[SCOFFS]

18:48.752 --> 18:50.504
Bessie: CHOCOLATE SYRUP.

18:53.173 --> 18:54.550
FINE, A POUND OF BACON.

18:54.633 --> 18:56.468
[TICKING]

18:56.552 --> 18:59.137
[RINGING]

18:59.221 --> 18:59.263
[GASPS]

19:01.932 --> 19:03.016
{\an3}OOH.

19:07.604 --> 19:09.898
[CHEWS NOISILY]

19:09.982 --> 19:11.525
MM, OOH.

19:11.608 --> 19:12.901
{\an3}DELICIOUS.

19:12.985 --> 19:15.571
IT'S HITTING ALL THE "Fs."

19:15.654 --> 19:18.282
FROZEN, FRUITY, FANCY.

19:18.365 --> 19:19.992
YOU'RE FORGIVEN.

19:20.075 --> 19:21.743
[CHEERING]

19:21.827 --> 19:23.036
Bessie: HEY, EVERYBODY.

19:23.120 --> 19:25.581
ICE CREAM LEAVING YOU COLD
THIS SUMMER?

19:25.664 --> 19:27.416
WHAT'S THAT, YOU WANT A CHANGE?

19:27.499 --> 19:29.918
WHY, TRY CHOCO-BANANAS.

19:30.002 --> 19:33.130
HOW CAN YOU RESIST
DELICIOUS FROZEN BANANAS?

19:33.213 --> 19:36.425
ALL OF SAN FRANCISCO
CAN'T BE WRONG.

19:36.508 --> 19:38.802
GET 'EM WHILE THEY'RE HOT-
I MEAN COLD.

19:38.886 --> 19:40.053
[♪...]

19:40.137 --> 19:41.847
[GROWLS]

19:46.685 --> 19:48.312
[THUDDING NOISE]

19:52.566 --> 19:54.610
WHAT'S THIS?

19:54.693 --> 19:56.612
[GROWLS AND GRUNTS]

19:56.695 --> 19:58.572
{\an1}WHAT, WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
A MESSAGE?

19:58.655 --> 20:00.032
THEY WANT TO TALK TO ME?

20:00.115 --> 20:01.742
THEY WANT TO TALK TO ME
ABOUT MY FROZEN BANANAS?

20:01.825 --> 20:03.368
{\an3}[GRUNTS]

20:12.336 --> 20:14.254
SO I HEAR YOU WANT TO
TALK BANANAS.

20:16.840 --> 20:18.425
THAT'S RIGHT,
WE MEAN NO DISRESPECT

20:18.508 --> 20:21.970
BUT I GOTTA TELL YOU, YOU KEEP
CUTTING INTO OUR PROFITS

20:22.054 --> 20:23.847
AND YOU'RE TREADING ON
THIN ITALIAN ICE.

20:23.931 --> 20:26.808
{\an4}YOU THINK YOU CAN JUST
COME OUT OF NOWHERE AND SELL
CHOCO-BANANAS ON OUR TURF?

20:26.892 --> 20:30.145
I'M NOT ABOVE COMPROMISE.

20:30.228 --> 20:32.940
ONE SEC WHILE I CONSULT WITH
MY ASSOCIATES.

20:33.023 --> 20:34.483
[WHISPERING INDISTINCTLY]

20:34.566 --> 20:37.069
{\an3}[BARKING]

20:37.152 --> 20:39.780
GENTLEMEN, I THINK
WE HAVE A PROPOSAL

20:39.863 --> 20:42.366
THAT WILL BE MUTUALLY BENEFICIAL
TO BOTH PARTIES.

20:42.449 --> 20:45.160
{\an5}THE ICE CREAM MAN'S ASSOCIATION
TAKES OVER THE DISTRIBUTION OF
CHOCO-BANANAS

20:45.243 --> 20:49.206
{\an5}AND IN RETURN, FULL ICE CREAM
TRUCK SERVICE IS RESTORED TO
OUR NEIGHBORHOOD.

20:50.374 --> 20:53.168
{\an1}I DON'T KNOW, BOSS, I DON'T
THINK SHE'S SO TOUGH.

20:53.251 --> 20:55.170
[CLAMORING]

20:55.253 --> 20:55.295
[CRUNCHING]

21:01.385 --> 21:01.426
[GASPS]

21:09.559 --> 21:11.520
{\an1}[CHEERING]

21:11.603 --> 21:13.647
OK, OK, WHERE WAS I?

21:13.730 --> 21:16.733
SO, [CHUCKLES], A LEPRECHAUN
WALKS INTO A BAR...

21:16.817 --> 21:19.194
OH, UGH, WAIT, OK,
START OVER, START OVER.

21:19.278 --> 21:22.030
OK, THERE'S A BAR AND...

21:22.114 --> 21:24.116
{\an5}SOMEONE COMES IN
AND ORDERS A MILKSHAKE
AND IT'S <i> NOT</i> A LEPRECHAUN.

21:24.199 --> 21:26.159
OH, WHY DO I KEEP SAYING THAT?

21:26.243 --> 21:29.663
[♪...]

22:06.491 --> 22:10.746
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
